%% Helpdesk agent state machine — four explicit terminal outcomes
%%
%% Reviewer narrative:
%%   "What stops this agent from running forever or filing the wrong ticket?"
%%   Every transition is labeled with the API call or guard that triggers it.
%%   Terminal outcomes are exhaustive: resolved · linked · filed · aborted.
stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR
    [*] --> Idle
    Idle --> Running: POST /agent/start[/stream]
    Running --> Running: tool_call → observation<br/>(retry_kb · web_search · search_dups)
    Running --> AwaitingUser: next_action = clarify<br/>SSE AgentTurn(question)
    AwaitingUser --> Running: POST /agent/resume[/stream]<br/>(checkpoint reloaded)
    AwaitingUser --> Aborted: POST /agent/abort
    Running --> Linked: search_dups returns match
    Running --> Resolved: next_action = resolved_by_agent
    Running --> Aborted: budget exhausted<br/>(max_steps · tokens · per-user-day)<br/>or HELPDESK_AGENT_KILL_SWITCH
    Running --> AwaitingConfirm: next_action = write_draft<br/>SSE AgentTurn(draft_ready)
    AwaitingConfirm --> Aborted: POST /agent/abort
    AwaitingConfirm --> Filing: POST /agent/confirm<br/>(HITL gate)
    Filing --> Filed: file_ticket success<br/>(redacted at boundary)
    Filing --> Aborted: file_ticket error
    Filed --> [*]
    Resolved --> [*]
    Linked --> [*]
    Aborted --> [*]

    note right of Filing
        file_ticket is reachable
        only via /agent/confirm.
        Redaction applied twice:
        once on draft, again on
        outbound issue body.
    end note

    note left of Running
        Bounded loop · LangGraph
        SqliteSaver checkpoint
        per session_id · 24h TTL
    end note
